{"questionId":"9073513","questionHtml":"<p>Outline how Hubble’s law is related to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">«Hubble’s » measure of v/recessional speed uses redshift which is </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math><br></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em><strong>OR<br></strong></em></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">redshift (</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">) of galaxies is proportional to distance «from earth»<br></span><em><strong>OR<br></strong></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">combines&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>H</mi><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em><strong>AND</strong></em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mi>c</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">into one expression, e.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>H</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></math>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle4\">✓</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle2\">OWTTE</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073513","referenceCode":"20N.3.SL.TZ0.16b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline how Hubble’s law is related to z.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics (Core topics)","D.3 – Cosmology","Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}